def: A substance, as salt, ammonium chloride, etc., whichcrystallizes with water of crystallization only at low temperatures,or below the freezing point of water. F. Guthrie.
To grind with the teeth, and with a crackling sound; tocraunch. [Prov. Eng. & Colloq. U.S.]

To cause to rest by soothing influences; to compose; to calm;to soothe; to quiet. " To lull him soft asleep." Spenser.Such sweet compulsion doth in music lie, To lull the daughters ofnecessity. Milton.
The four "liberal arts," arithmetic, music, geometry, andastronomy; -- so called by the schoolmen. See Trivium.
The quality or state of being orthognathous. Huxley.
To make merry with; to make jokes upon; to rally; to banter;as, to joke a comrade.
The state or condition of being bald; as, baldness of the head;baldness of style.This gives to their syntax a peculiar character of simplicity andbaldness. W. D. Whitney.
The division of the terms of an equation by a known quantitythat is involved in the first term. [Obs.]
The quality or states of being spiral.
To make verses.I'll versify in spite, and do my best. Dryden.
Cold; chilly. Bailey. Algid cholera (Med.), Asiatic cholera.
A collection of, or a treatise on, maxims, grave sentences, orreflections. [Obs.] Milton.
